title: Le Halua Le
subTitle: Sonali moves to the city to earn money and repay her debts to her landlord. She fakes a marriage with Suvojeet, a struggling artist, in order to get low-priced accommodation.

title: Bhalobasi Sudhu Tomake
subTitle: Pooja is the daughter of a rich businessman, Maitreyee, who falls in love with Bijay. Things take a turn for the worse when the union leader at Maitrayee's factory is murdered and Bijay is the main suspect.

title: Shiv Shakti
subTitle: Parvati is shocked after witnessing Lord Shiva's ruthlessness. Tarakasura seizes the opportunity to abduct Parvati and make her his queen.

title: Jamai No 1
subTitle: A businessman weds his two eldest daughters to men who now depend on him. However, things take a turn when his third daughter marries a thief.

title: Professor Shanku O El Dorado
subTitle: Genius inventor Professor Shonku heads into the Amazon in search of the mythical El Dorado, with the help of Nakurbabu and his supernatural powers.

title: Manik
subTitle: Samir Mitra impersonates his deceased friend to get a job. Later, when he falls in love with his employer's daughter and mutual relations meet, his identity is questioned.

title: Dada Thakur
subTitle: Gita plans to reunite with her long-estranged father, not knowing that he is waiting for her younger sister, Mita, to return. The two siblings then struggle to win back his trust.

title: Chandra Mallika
subTitle: A man defies his wealthy father and marries a woman from a simple background. However, his father is determined to break up the relationship.

title: Josh
subTitle: Indra, a care-free college student, tries to save his best friend's sister, Anuradha, from a dangerous family dispute, but his efforts lead to unexpected and worsening complications.

title: Naga Panchami
subTitle: A man kills his sister and throws her family into disarray. However, his sister's daughter, a shape-shifting snake, is determined to seek revenge.

title: Naga Panchami
subTitle: A man kills his sister and throws her family into disarray. However, his sister's daughter, a shape-shifting snake, is determined to seek revenge.

title: Smritimedur
subTitle: Ayan, a heartbroken student, finds solace in Smriti, a young widow, during a trip to North Bengal. Subsequently, they both learn to love again.

title: Shiv Shakti
subTitle: Affected by Mainavati's warning, Parvati becomes hesitant to marry Lord Shiva and reconsiders her decision, unaware that her actions satisfy Mainavati.

title: Ke Tumi
subTitle: Sudha, a girl belonging to a middle-class family, is forced to marry a smuggler but she boards a train to escape. However, an accident changes her life entirely.

title: Daidaitwa
subTitle: Ronojoy saves Kaberi after he finds her abandoned and in a dangerous condition. However, by saving her, he puts his personal life and family in jeopardy.

title: Dadu No.1
subTitle: Bhawani Chatterjee, a rich businessman, tries to play the matchmaker between his employee, Mamta, who is a widow and grandson.

title: Awara
subTitle: Surya falls in love with a girl and follows her to Kolkata, where she stays with her rowdy elder brother. Later, he decides to rescue her when he discovers that a gangster wants to marry her forcibly.

title: Sejo Bou
subTitle: A poor man falls in love with a girl belonging to a wealthy family. In an attempt to separate them, the man is sent abroad. However, the couple's destiny intervenes, striving to bring them together.

title: Greftaar
subTitle: Arun Roy, a police sub-inspector, comes face-to-face with a corrupt political leader, Indrajit, and stands up to him. As a result, his father is humiliated and suspended from the police.

title: Pratarak
subTitle: A young man leaves his wealthy father to work in the city without knowing of a conspiracy by a trusted manager to take over his parent's business.

title: Pratarak
subTitle: A young man leaves his wealthy father to work in the city without knowing of a conspiracy by a trusted manager to take over his parent's business.

title: Taan
subTitle: When a photographer goes missing in the Sundarbans, his friend, Lisa, goes to look for him. Her journey brings her face-to-face with the women in the region who are forced into prostitution.

title: Shiv Shakti
subTitle: Parvati agrees to marry as she gives the utmost importance to her parents' wishes. However, Narada Muni is determined to change Parvati's decision.

title: Aagoon
subTitle: A childless couple adopts an orphan whose parents died under mysterious circumstances. Eventually, the orphan grows up and embarks on a quest to uncover the truth behind his parents' suspicious death.

title: SWAMIR ADESH
subTitle: Sunil, an honest judge, abandons his pregnant wife due to a misunderstanding created by his aunt. However, years later, he fights a case in his daughter's favour and reunites with his family.

title: Streer Maryada
subTitle: Saptami, an orphan, marries a rich doctor who spends most of his time at work. A few days into the marriage, her in-laws start harassing her but things go awry when they humiliate her brother.

title: Minister Phatakesto
subTitle: Fatakeshto, an MLA turned home minister, vows to rescue the government from a massive financial loss while political thugs create several hurdles for him.

title: Jiban Niye Khela
subTitle: In the distant village of Dharampur, Dr Subhankar Sanyal fights the bureaucracy and brings justice to the lives of his patients.

title: Wanted
subTitle: The police kill Shibu, an innocent man, after mistaking him to be his lookalike Raja, an assassin. To escape from the police, Raja starts living with Shibu's parents as their son.

title: Bornoporichoy
subTitle: Dhananjoy, a police detective, goes on a desperate lookout for Arko, a man who murders people, taking inspiration from the five elements- Earth, Water, Wind, Sky, and Fire.
